works.description: At its inaugural Villa d’Este sale in Cernobbio, Italy on May 21, RM Auctions is going to offer six iconic concepts developed by the Italian design and coach-building company Bertone. These classic concept cars come from the Bertone Museum collection that is being liquidated as part of the Bertone’s recent financial reorganization. The six cars up for grabs include the 1967 Lamborghini Marzal, 1970 Lancia Stratos HF Zero, 1963 Chevrolet Testudo, 1974 Lamborghini Bravo, 1980 Lamborghini Athon and the 1978 Lancia Sibilo
